Overall Condition: This handgun retains about 95% of its metal finish. There is light wear from normal operational use. The exterior of the gun exhibits very light sign of use. The markings are clear. Overall, this handgun rates in about Fine condition, excellent if not for the bore. Mechanics: The action functions correctly. If you have ever owned a HK product you know that they don’t put their name on junk, nor are they cheap by any means. The guns manufactured here in the states are great, but the German manufactured guns tend to demand a slightly higher premium because of the assumed higher quality of the finial product.
